This paper is primarily focused on the development of a programming framework for safe robotics systems, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the integration of runtime assurance techniques, which involves software engineering principles (cs.SE) and system-level considerations (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques for autonomous robots suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper addresses safety concerns, which could be relevant to the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
